projects.description:
The project 'Business research' is the construction and presentation of a research project in a realistic setting and with a practical and theoretical justification. 
The project was conducted on the company Nivea. 
The research question was: ''How can Nivea improve their customer satisfaction?'' 
The core objectives of the project being: 
• develop and execute a survey based on a questionnaire;
• process and analyze quantitative data resulting from research;
• both understand and apply multivariate and univariate statistical calculations and methods; 
• assess the validity and reliability of the collected data; 
• use commonly used software such as SPSS for research purposes;
• use charts and tables correctly in both written and oral communication; 
• present the results of the research in both written and oral form.

The quarter Business Plan project contributes to the development of marketing, intercultural management and financial and management accounting knowledge and skills. The project aids in discovering that running a business successfully means that you will need to have a plan, i.e. a budget and brings more insight into the financial aspects of running a business. 
The core objectives are: 
• make a budget for a small/medium size company;
• construct a financial report containing a Balance Sheet, Profit & Loss Account and a Cashflow statement;
• translate events into financial data;
• Analyze financial aspects to interpret the financial situation of the company in the light of investment decisions; 
• use Excel as a tool to calculate/collect data and to deliver financial reports; 
• to summarize your personal and professional development to grow as a person and a business professional; 
• present the results of the project in writing and a separate Excel file;
• advise upon opening a new business in another European country.
